benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/search - Search custom fields by type, name and optional value

covered: Valid GET behavior with multiple parameter combinations returning 200 and correctly filtered CustomField objects
No-parameter fetch returns all custom fields (TC01) and schema conformance
Pagination scenarios covered (offset/limit): TC07, TC21, TC22, TC31
Audit parameter handling (FULL, MINIMAL, NONE) and integration with audit log service (TC08-12, TC32, TC33)
Error handling for invalid inputs: invalid objectType (TC13), invalid offset (TC14), invalid limit (TC15), invalid audit (TC16), SQL injection (TC19), XSS (TC20)
Empty/results and state variation tests: empty DB (TC28), partially populated DB (TC29), empty results when no match (TC11)
Regression tests for fieldName filtering and FULL audit correctness (TC25-26)
Performance tests for timing under normal/peak load (TC24, TC31)
Security tests: SQL injection (TC19) and XSS (TC20)
Dependency/service integration and degradation tests (TC18, TC32, TC33)
gaps: Rate limiting tests are not covered (throttling, quotas, burst handling)
Caching behavior not tested (ETag / Cache-Control headers and cache validation)
403 Forbidden or insufficient-permission scenarios beyond 401 are not explicitly tested
Tests for invalid/expired authentication tokens or varying auth schemes could be expanded
recommendations: Add rate-limiting/throttling scenarios to ensure multiple rapid requests are handled gracefully
Add caching header verification tests (ETag, Cache-Control) and cache invalidation behavior
Include tests for 403 Forbidden due to insufficient permissions and invalid/expired tokens to broaden auth coverage
Consider additional edge-case tests for very large datasets with concurrent pagination and more diverse objectTypes to further stress-test pagination and filters
